caption;Versi 2
no;1
p;Why did Jesus give up heaven’s glory
p;For this world of sin and misery?
p;Why did Jesus suffer in the garden,
p;Drain the bitter cup of agony?
p;Why did Jesus stand in Pilate’s judgement hall,
p;Wear that cruel crown of thorns so patiently?
p;Why did Jesus give His life to save me?
p;It was love, God’s wondrous love for me!
empty
no;2
p;Why does Jesus lift me when I stumble
p;Take my hand whene’er I go astray?
p;Give me strength I need for each tomorrow,
p;Grace to face the trials of the day?
p;Why does Jesus share the load I cannot bear,
p;Fill my soul with peace and joy beyond degree?
p;And why does He watch o’er me and keep me?
p;It was love, God’s wondrous love for me!
